OL,3,CFarmer recalls emotional and financial
OL,4,Ctoll of losing sheep in dog attacks
OL,6,F"Farmers across the country are living
OL,7,Fin fear of repeat attacks, which cause
OL,8,Fhorrific suffering to livestock and
OL,9,Fcan traumatise all involved in dealing
OL,10,Fwith the aftermath. Anecdotally, we've
OL,11,Fheard of many incidents where dogs
OL,12,Fhave injured and killed sheep and the
OL,13,Fowner is powerless to stop it or is
OL,14,Fnowhere to be seen.
OL,16,F"Ignorance isn't bliss when it comes
OL,17,Fto dog attacks on livestock;
OL,18,Fregardless of size, breed or
OL,19,Ftemperament, all dogs are capable of
OL,20,Fchasing, injuring and killing farm
OL,21,Fanimals."
