OL,3,CFarmer recalls emotional and financial
OL,4,Ctoll of losing sheep in dog attacks
OL,6,F"The Order also states that if a dog
OL,7,Fworries sheep (attacks or kills sheep
OL,8,For chases them in a way that may cause
OL,9,Finjury, suffering or financial loss to
OL,10,Ftheir owner) the person in charge of
OL,11,Fthat dog is guilty of an offence. The
OL,12,Fpenalty for this offence is a fine of
OL,13,Fup to #1,000 and the court can also
OL,14,Forder the destruction of the dog.
OL,16,F"My Department continues to highlight
OL,17,Fthe need for dog owners to comply with
OL,18,Fthe law on livestock worrying,
OL,19,Fincluding the need to have control
OL,20,Fover their dog at all times,
OL,21,Fespecially in the countryside.
